{
  "video_id": "uTEL8Ff1Zvk",
  "title": "What's the Difference Between DevOps and SRE? (class SRE implements DevOps)",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 1869.0,
      "end_time": 2910.0,
      "text": "LIZ FONG-JONES: Hi there."
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 2910.0,
      "end_time": 6280.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m Liz, a Site Reliability Engineer, or SRE, at Google."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6280.0,
      "end_time": 7860.0,
      "text": "And I teach Google Cloud customers"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 7860.0,
      "end_time": 10159.0,
      "text": "how to build and operate reliable services."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 10159.0,
      "end_time": 11700.0,
      "text": "SETH VARGO: And I&#39;m Seth, a Developer"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 11700.0,
      "end_time": 14879.0,
      "text": "Advocate at Google focused on infrastructure and operations."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 14880.0,
      "end_time": 17890.0,
      "text": "And Liz and I are here to settle things once and for all."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 17890.0,
      "end_time": 20375.0,
      "text": "Which is better, DevOps or SRE?"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 20375.0,
      "end_time": 21750.0,
      "text": "LIZ FONG-JONES: Whoa there, Seth."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 21750.0,
      "end_time": 22494.0,
      "text": "Hold on a second."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 22494.0,
      "end_time": 23910.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m not sure you&#39;re really looking"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 23910.0,
      "end_time": 25440.0,
      "text": "at this in the right way."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 25440.0,
      "end_time": 27900.0,
      "text": "But first of all, maybe we should clarify some things."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 27900.0,
      "end_time": 29577.0,
      "text": "What do you think DevOps is?"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 29577.0,
      "end_time": 31410.0,
      "text": "SETH VARGO: So that&#39;s a great question, Liz."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 31410.0,
      "end_time": 34170.0,
      "text": "Back in the day, operators and developers"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 34170.0,
      "end_time": 35580.0,
      "text": "had a lot of contention."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 35580.0,
      "end_time": 37830.0,
      "text": "Developers used to throw their code"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 37830.0,
      "end_time": 40233.0,
      "text": "over the metaphorical wall, and operators"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 40234.0,
      "end_time": 42150.0,
      "text": "were responsible for keeping that code running"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 42150.0,
      "end_time": 43320.0,
      "text": "in production."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 43320.0,
      "end_time": 45420.0,
      "text": "Operators had little understanding of the code"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 45420.0,
      "end_time": 47610.0,
      "text": "bases, and developers had little understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 47610.0,
      "end_time": 49289.0,
      "text": "of operational practices."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 49289.0,
      "end_time": 51330.0,
      "text": "But developers were concerned with shipping code,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 51330.0,
      "end_time": 54100.0,
      "text": "and operators were concerned with reliability."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 54100.0,
      "end_time": 55800.0,
      "text": "This misalignment often caused tension"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 55800.0,
      "end_time": 57739.0,
      "text": "within the organization."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 57739.0,
      "end_time": 59779.0,
      "text": "LIZ FONG-JONES: So if I understand you correctly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 59780.0,
      "end_time": 60970.0,
      "text": "you&#39;re saying that the developers were"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 60970.0,
      "end_time": 63700.0,
      "text": "responsible for features, and the operators"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 63700.0,
      "end_time": 66100.0,
      "text": "were responsible for stability, meaning the developers wanted"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 66100.0,
      "end_time": 68410.0,
      "text": "to move faster to get their features out faster"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 68410.0,
      "end_time": 71786.0,
      "text": "and the operators wanted to move slower to keep things stable?"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 71787.0,
      "end_time": 73870.0,
      "text": "I could see how that would cause a lot of tension."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 73870.0,
      "end_time": 74830.0,
      "text": "SETH VARGO: Exactly."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 74830.0,
      "end_time": 78370.0,
      "text": "So DevOps is a set of practices and a culture designed"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 78370.0,
      "end_time": 81850.0,
      "text": "to break down those barriers between developers, operators,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 81850.0,
      "end_time": 84130.0,
      "text": "and other parts of the organization."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 84130.0,
      "end_time": 87259.0,
      "text": "I break DevOps down into five key areas."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 87260.0,
      "end_time": 90220.0,
      "text": "First, reduce organizational silence."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 90220.0,
      "end_time": 92289.0,
      "text": "By breaking down barriers across teams,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 92290.0,
      "end_time": 95280.0,
      "text": "we can increase collaboration and thorough put."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 95280.0,
      "end_time": 98380.0,
      "text": "Second, accept failure as normal."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 98380.0,
      "end_time": 100910.0,
      "text": "Computers are inherently unreliable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 100910.0,
      "end_time": 102729.0,
      "text": "so we can&#39;t expect perfection."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 102730.0,
      "end_time": 104920.0,
      "text": "And when we introduce humans into the system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 104920.0,
      "end_time": 107480.0,
      "text": "we get even more imperfection."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 107480.0,
      "end_time": 110300.0,
      "text": "Third, implement gradual change."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 110300.0,
      "end_time": 114350.0,
      "text": "Not only are small, incremental changes easier to review,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 114350.0,
      "end_time": 117229.0,
      "text": "but in the event that a gradual change does"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 117230.0,
      "end_time": 119210.0,
      "text": "make a bug in production, it allows"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 119210.0,
      "end_time": 121130.0,
      "text": "us to reduce our mean time to recover,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 121130.0,
      "end_time": 123500.0,
      "text": "making it simple to roll back."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 123500.0,
      "end_time": 127340.0,
      "text": "Fourth, we need to leverage tooling and automation."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 127340.0,
      "end_time": 130430.0,
      "text": "And fifth, we need to measure everything."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 130430.0,
      "end_time": 132920.0,
      "text": "Measurement is a critical gauge for success."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 132920.0,
      "end_time": 135470.0,
      "text": "And without a way to measure if our first four pillars"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 135470.0,
      "end_time": 139800.0,
      "text": "were successful, we would have no way of knowing if they were."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 139800.0,
      "end_time": 143990.0,
      "text": "So, Liz, you&#39;ve been an SRE at Google for over 10 years now."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 143990.0,
      "end_time": 146570.0,
      "text": "Do you think any of the way that I described DevOps aligns"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 146570.0,
      "end_time": 148790.0,
      "text": "with your experience as an SRE?"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 148790.0,
      "end_time": 150890.0,
      "text": "LIZ FONG-JONES: It&#39;s sounding very familiar."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 150890.0,
      "end_time": 154119.0,
      "text": "Because, if you think about DevOps as a philosophy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 154120.0,
      "end_time": 158270.0,
      "text": "SRE is a prescriptive way of accomplishing that philosophy."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 158270.0,
      "end_time": 161960.0,
      "text": "So if DevOps were an interface in programming language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 161960.0,
      "end_time": 165200.0,
      "text": "you might almost say that SRE is a concrete class that"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 165200.0,
      "end_time": 166910.0,
      "text": "implements DevOps."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 166910.0,
      "end_time": 168930.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s take a look at how that is."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 168930.0,
      "end_time": 171230.0,
      "text": "So, Seth, when you talked about eliminating"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 171230.0,
      "end_time": 173390.0,
      "text": "organizational silos, what I thought about"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 173390.0,
      "end_time": 175609.0,
      "text": "is the fact that we share ownership of production"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 175610.0,
      "end_time": 176900.0,
      "text": "with our developers."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 176900.0,
      "end_time": 178400.0,
      "text": "And we use the same tooling in order"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 178400.0,
      "end_time": 181100.0,
      "text": "to make sure everyone has the same view and same approach"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 181100.0,
      "end_time": 182522.0,
      "text": "to working with production."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 182522.0,
      "end_time": 184730.0,
      "text": "When you talked about accepting accidents and failure"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 184730.0,
      "end_time": 187160.0,
      "text": "as normal, what I thought about is the fact that--"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 187160.0,
      "end_time": 189740.0,
      "text": "similar to many DevOps practitioners--"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 189740.0,
      "end_time": 191300.0,
      "text": "we have blameless postmortems, where"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 191300.0,
      "end_time": 194240.0,
      "text": "we make sure that the failures that happen in our production"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 194240.0,
      "end_time": 197600.0,
      "text": "systems don&#39;t happen the exact same way more than once."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 197600.0,
      "end_time": 200120.0,
      "text": "And we accept the failures as normal by encoding"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 200120.0,
      "end_time": 203000.0,
      "text": "a concept of an error budget of how much the system is allowed"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 203000.0,
      "end_time": 204290.0,
      "text": "to go out of spec."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 204290.0,
      "end_time": 206941.0,
      "text": "And then third, we talked about making gradual changes."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 206941.0,
      "end_time": 208940.0,
      "text": "And when you said that, I thought about the fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 208940.0,
      "end_time": 210515.0,
      "text": "that we canary things, that we roll"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 210515.0,
      "end_time": 212390.0,
      "text": "things out to a small percentage of the fleet"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 212390.0,
      "end_time": 214159.0,
      "text": "before we move them out for all users."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 214159.0,
      "end_time": 216200.0,
      "text": "And then fourth, when you talked about leveraging"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 216200.0,
      "end_time": 218209.0,
      "text": "tooling and automation, what I thought about"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 218210.0,
      "end_time": 220250.0,
      "text": "is the fact that we try to eliminate manual work"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 220250.0,
      "end_time": 221310.0,
      "text": "as much as possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 221310.0,
      "end_time": 223970.0,
      "text": "So we measure how much toil we have,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 223970.0,
      "end_time": 226522.0,
      "text": "and then we try to automate this year&#39;s job away."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 226522.0,
      "end_time": 228980.0,
      "text": "And then fifth, when you talked about measuring everything,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 228980.0,
      "end_time": 230780.0,
      "text": "I thought about exactly that measurement"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 230780.0,
      "end_time": 232820.0,
      "text": "of measuring the amount of toil that we have"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 232820.0,
      "end_time": 235849.0,
      "text": "and measuring the reliability and health of our systems."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 235849.0,
      "end_time": 237140.0,
      "text": "SETH VARGO: I really like that."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 237140.0,
      "end_time": 239390.0,
      "text": "Class SRE implements DevOps."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 239390.0,
      "end_time": 241339.0,
      "text": "We should get that on a shirt or something."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 241340.0,
      "end_time": 244700.0,
      "text": "But just like a class in a programming language,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 244700.0,
      "end_time": 246440.0,
      "text": "there might be additional functions or methods"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 246440.0,
      "end_time": 248930.0,
      "text": "that don&#39;t necessarily correspond to that interface."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 248930.0,
      "end_time": 251390.0,
      "text": "Or the class might implement multiple interfaces."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 251390.0,
      "end_time": 252923.0,
      "text": "Do you think SRE is like that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 252924.0,
      "end_time": 254340.0,
      "text": "LIZ FONG-JONES: I absolutely think"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 254340.0,
      "end_time": 256190.0,
      "text": "that&#39;s the case because of the fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 256190.0,
      "end_time": 259370.0,
      "text": "that SRE doesn&#39;t do things in the exact same way"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 259370.0,
      "end_time": 261920.0,
      "text": "that other people that implement DevOps elsewhere"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 261920.00000000003,
      "end_time": 263670.0,
      "text": "might want to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 263670.0,
      "end_time": 266330.0,
      "text": "So we&#39;ll talk a little bit more about those differences,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 266330.0,
      "end_time": 269600.0,
      "text": "such as how exactly SLOs work, which"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 269600.0,
      "end_time": 272270.0,
      "text": "are a very specific concept that we implement in order"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 272270.0,
      "end_time": 274640.0,
      "text": "to make SRE successful."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 274640.0,
      "end_time": 275390.0,
      "text": "SETH VARGO: Great."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 275390.0,
      "end_time": 276919.0,
      "text": "Well, that settles it, then."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 276920.0,
      "end_time": 280730.0,
      "text": "It turns out that DevOps and SRE aren&#39;t two competing methods,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 280730.0,
      "end_time": 282800.0,
      "text": "but rather close friends designed"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 282800.0,
      "end_time": 285170.0,
      "text": "to help break down organizational barriers"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 285170.0,
      "end_time": 287720.0,
      "text": "to deliver better software faster."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 287720.0,
      "end_time": 289486.0,
      "text": "Thank you, everyone, for watching."
    },
    {
